Excalidraw has an excellent support for a stylus (I am using Microsoft Surface Pen with Surface Pro 7). I would like to use it for taking quick notes, but right now the eraser side of the Surface Pen does not work.

This issue is similar to #5166, but with a difference:

- In #5166, the request seems to be about holding a button on the side of the pen to erase.

  <img width="609" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/193136/172116655-6021eebb-12e4-401d-b40c-32d4b0791e6b.png">

- This issue is about using the eraser side of Microsoft Surface Pen Eraser.

  <img width="766" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/193136/172116799-e2cba672-ff78-4f13-8d58-319779ab61ec.png">

It would be great if its support is built in to the app.

## Workaround

I created a userscript that will temporarily switch to Eraser mode while the eraser side of the pen is pushed against the screen, and deactivates the Eraser mode upon release. Here’s a demo video:

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/193136/172117163-2ef7e3cf-08d4-40c9-a186-8c8ad9edbf08.mp4

Here’s a userscript. I have tested this with Tampermonkey in Microsoft Edge.

```js
// ==UserScript==
// @name         Excalidraw Microsoft Surface Pen Eraser Support
// @namespace    https://dt.in.th/
// @version      0.1
// @description  Adds Microsoft Surface Pen Eraser support to Excalidraw
// @author       Thai Pangsakulyanont (dtinth)
// @match        https://excalidraw.com/
// @icon         https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=excalidraw.com
// @grant        none
// ==/UserScript==

(function() {
    'use strict';

    let activated
    function handlePointer(e) {
        const isEraser = e.pointerType === 'pen' && e.buttons & 32
        const isPenActive = document.querySelector('[data-testid="freedraw"]')?.checked
        if (!activated && isEraser && isPenActive) {
            document.querySelector('button[aria-label="Eraser"]')?.click()
            activated = true

            // Force Excalidraw to recognize this as a normal button.
            // https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/blob/4a9fac2d1e5c4fac334201ef53c6f5d2b5f6f9f5/src/components/App.tsx#L2945-L2951
            Object.defineProperty(e, 'button', {
                value: 0,
                writable: false
            });
        }
        if (activated && !isEraser) {
            // Clicking the eraser button again will switch back to the last used tool
            // https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/issues/4978
            document.querySelector('button[aria-label="Eraser"]')?.click()
            activated = false
        }
    }

    window.addEventListener('pointerdown', handlePointer, { capture: true })
    window.addEventListener('pointermove', handlePointer, { capture: true })
})();
```

